###AWS TECHNICAL ESSENTIALS
CLOUD COMPUTING- This is the on demand delivery of IT resources over the internet with pay as you go pricing.
Cloud computing deployment models- On-Premises(Private). Cloud(Public), Hybrid(private and public)
Six advantages of cloud computing [1. Pay as you go, 2.Benefit from massive economies of scale, 3. Stop guessing capacity, 4. Increase speed and agility, 5. Realize cost saving, 6. Go global in minutes.]
###AWS GLOBAL INFRASTRUTURE

Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (Amazon EC2) is a web service that provides resizable compute capacity in the cloud.
Amazon EC2 currently supports a variety of operating systems including: • Amazon Linux • Ubuntu• Windows Server• MacOS• Red Hat Enterprise Linux• SUSE Linux Enterprise Server • Fedora • Debian • CentOS • Gentoo Linux• Oracle Linux• FreeBSD

Preconfigured templates for your instances are known as Amazon Machine Images (AMIs).

You can logically manage your infrastructure through the AWS Application Program Interface, or API. You can create, delete, or change any AWS resource using API calls.
Three main ways API calls are used in AWS are through the AWS Management Console, the AWS Command Line Interface, and the AWS Software Development Kits, or SDKs. 
